properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 16 at 9:54AM PST until January 16 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches. Storm
total accumulations of 2 to 6 inches, with highest amounts above
2000 feet.

* WHERE...Southwestern Humboldt and Southeastern Mendocino
Interior Counties. Highways impacted include higher elevation
portions of Highway 101 and Highway 20.

* WHEN...Through 4 PM Thursday. Heaviest, steadiest snow through
midday. Precipitation becoming more showery but still
occasionally heavy this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult. Chain requirements or
occasional road closures are possible.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state of California can be
obtained by calling 1-800-GAS-ROAD.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON ABOVE 1500 FEET
